📌 Key Learning (Day 24)

This problem introduces the Minimax Dynamic Programming pattern.

The DP state is:

dp[start][end]

which represents the minimum cost required to guarantee a win for the interval [start, end].

For every possible guess k:

cost = k + max(
    dp[start][k-1],
    dp[k+1][end]
)
We use max() because the hidden number could be in the more expensive interval (worst case).
We use min() over all possible guesses to minimize our guaranteed cost.
